# Scrapy Basics

# shell: 
  Starts the Scrapy shell for the given URL (if given) or empty if no URL is given

scrapy shell

# fetch
# Downloads the given URL using the Scrapy downloader and writes the contents to standard output.

fetch("https://www.amazon.in/")

# View :
# Opens the given URL in a browser, as your Scrapy spider would “see” it. Sometimes spiders see pages differently from regular users, so     
# this can be used to check what the spider “sees” and confirm it’s what you expect.

view(response)

response.css(".title::text").extract()

